<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="5" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C114/445d</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>)<note n="9" xml:id="d5fn9">Also Minister to Luxemburg.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-02-12"><hi rend="italic">February 12,
                                    1926</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 226</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am enclosing, for transmission to Baron
                            Raymond de Waha, still accredited as Chargé d’Affaires of Luxemburg to
                            the United States, a note<note n="10" xml:id="d5fn10">Text identical
                                with that of the note to the Austrian Minister, February 12, <ref target="#pg_3">p. 3</ref>.</note> concerning the conditions,
                            reservations and understandings contained in the Resolution of the
                            Senate, dated January 27, 1926, for the adherence by the United States
                            to the Protocol of Signature and Statute of the Permanent Court of
                            International Justice.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frank B. Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>